S"{{Infobox congressman\n| name        =Rick W. Allen\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = \n| state       = \n| office      = Member-elect of the<br>[[U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[Georgia's 12th congressional district|Georgia's 12th district]]\n| term_start  = January 3, 2015\n| term_end    =\n| succeeding  = [[John Barrow (U.S. politician)|John Barrow]]\n| succeeded   = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1951|11|7}}\n| birth_place = [[Augusta, Georgia]], U.S.\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| birthname   = \n| nationality = [[United States|American]]\n| party       = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| residence   = [[Augusta, Georgia]]\n| alma_mater  = [[Auburn University]]\n| occupation  = }}\n\n'''Richard W. Allen''' (born November 7, 1951) is an American politician who was elected to serve [[Georgia's 12th congressional district]] in the [[United States House of Representatives elections, 2014]]. He will take office on January 3, 2015.\n\n==Career==\nAllen attended [[Auburn University]] and earned a degree in building construction. He is the founder of R.W. Allen and Associates, a construction company headquartered in Augusta.<ref>http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/136062/rick-allen#.VFlwdfTF_Zk</ref>\n\nAllen ran against [[John Barrow (U.S. politician)|John Barrow]] in the [[United States House of Representatives elections in Georgia, 2014|2014 election]] for {{ushr|GA|12}} in the [[United States House of Representatives]]. Allen defeated Barrow in the November election, in a result considered an upset.<ref>http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2014/11/04/tonights-rolling-blog-cnn-exit-polls-put-georgia-u-s-senate-race-at-49-48/</ref><ref>http://www.ajc.com/news/news/state-regional-govt-politics/rick-allen-upsets-john-barrow-for-georgia/nhzbx/</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAllen lives in [[Augusta, Georgia]]. A [[Methodist]], he is married to Robin and has four children.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{CongLinks|votesmart=136062}}\n*[http://www.rickwallen.com/ 2014 campaign website]\n\n<!--{{S-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{USRepSuccessionBox |\n  state=Georgia|\n  district=12 |\n  before=[[John Barrow (U.S. politician)|John Barrow]] |\n  start=2015\n}}\n{{S-end}}-->\n\n{{Persondata <!-- Metadata: see [[Wikipedia:Persondata]]. -->\n| NAME              =Allen, Rick W.\n| ALTERNATIVE NAMES =\n| SHORT DESCRIPTION = American politician\n| DATE OF BIRTH     =\n| PLACE OF BIRTH    =\n| DATE OF DEATH     =\n| PLACE OF DEATH    =\n}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Allen, Rick}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Augusta, Georgia]]\n[[Category:Georgia (U.S. state) Republicans]]\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Auburn University alumni]]\n[[Category:Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from Georgia (U.S. state)]]"
